name: Shape
description: A shape is a collection of constraints that may be targeted for certain nodes.

name: Node shape
description: A node shape is a shape that specifies constraint that need to be met with respect to focus nodes.

name: Property shape
description: A property shape is a shape that specifies constraints on the values of a focus node for a given property or path.

name: Severity
description: The class of validation result severity levels, including violation and warning levels.

name: Node kind
description: The class of all node kinds, including sh:BlankNode, sh:IRI, sh:Literal or the combinations of these: sh:BlankNodeOrIRI, sh:BlankNodeOrLiteral, sh:IRIOrLiteral.

name: Validation report
description: The class of SHACL validation reports.

name: Validation result
description: The class of validation results.

name: Abstract result
description: The base class of validation results, typically not instantiated directly.

name: Constraint component
description: The class of constraint components.

name: Parameterizable
description: Superclass of components that can take parameters, especially functions and constraint components.

name: Parameter
description: The class of parameter declarations, consisting of a path predicate and (possibly) information about allowed value type, cardinality and other characteristics.

name: Validator
description: The class of validators, which provide instructions on how to process a constraint definition. This class serves as base class for the SPARQL-based validators and other possible implementations.

name: SPARQL ASK validator
description: The class of validators based on SPARQL ASK queries. The queries are evaluated for each value node and are supposed to return true if the given node conforms.

name: SPARQL ASK executable
description: The class of SPARQL executables that are based on an ASK query.

name: SPARQL SELECT validator
description: The class of validators based on SPARQL SELECT queries. The queries are evaluated for each focus node and are supposed to produce bindings for all focus nodes that do not conform.

name: SPARQL SELECT executable
description: The class of SPARQL executables based on a SELECT query.

name: SPARQL executable
description: The class of resources that encapsulate a SPARQL query.

name: SPARQL CONSTRUCT executable
description: The class of SPARQL executables that are based on a CONSTRUCT query.

name: SPARQL UPDATE executable
description: The class of SPARQL executables based on a SPARQL UPDATE.

name: Prefix declaration
description: The class of prefix declarations, consisting of pairs of a prefix with a namespace.

name: SPARQL constraint
description: The class of constraints based on SPARQL SELECT queries.

name: Property group
description: Instances of this class represent groups of property shapes that belong together.

name: Target
description: The base class of targets such as those based on SPARQL queries.

name: Target type
description: The (meta) class for parameterizable targets.	Instances of this are instantiated as values of the sh:target property.

name: SPARQL target
description: The class of targets that are based on SPARQL queries.

name: SPARQL target type
description: The (meta) class for parameterizable targets that are based on SPARQL queries.

name: Function
description: The class of SHACL functions.

name: SPARQL function
description: A function backed by a SPARQL query - either ASK or SELECT.

name: Result annotation
description: A class of result annotations, which define the rules to derive the values of a given annotation property as extra values for a validation result.

name: Rule
description: The class of SHACL rules. Never instantiated directly.

name: A rule based on triple (subject, predicate, object) pattern.
SPARQL CONSTRUCT rule
description: The class of SHACL rules based on SPARQL CONSTRUCT queries.

name: JavaScript executable
description: Abstract base class of resources that declare an executable JavaScript.

name: JavaScript target
description: The class of targets that are based on JavaScript functions.

name: JavaScript target type
description: The (meta) class for parameterizable targets that are based on JavaScript functions.

name: JavaScript-based constraint
description: The class of constraints backed by a JavaScript function.

name: JavaScript library
description: Represents a JavaScript library, typically identified by one or more URLs of files to include.

name: JavaScript function
description: The class of SHACL functions that execute a JavaScript function when called.

name: JavaScript rule
description: The class of SHACL rules expressed using JavaScript.

name: JavaScript validator
description: A SHACL validator based on JavaScript. This can be used to declare SHACL constraint components that perform JavaScript-based validation when used.

name: prefix
description: The prefix of a prefix declaration.

name: namespace
description: The namespace associated with a prefix in a prefix declaration.

name: declare
description: Links a resource with its namespace prefix declarations.

name: suggested shapes graph
description: Suggested shapes graphs for this ontology. The values of this property may be used in the absence of specific sh:shapesGraph statements.

name: deactivated
description: If set to true then all nodes conform to this.

name: target class
description: Links a shape to a class, indicating that all instances of the class must conform to the shape.

name: target node
description: Links a shape to individual nodes, indicating that these nodes must conform to the shape.

name: target objects of
description: Links a shape to a property, indicating that all all objects of triples that have the given property as their predicate must conform to the shape.

name: target subjects of
description: Links a shape to a property, indicating that all subjects of triples that have the given property as their predicate must conform to the shape.

name: message
description: A human-readable message (possibly with placeholders for variables) explaining the cause of the result.

name: severity
description: Defines the severity that validation results produced by a shape must have. Defaults to sh:Violation.

name: conforms
description: True if the validation did not produce any validation results, and false otherwise.

name: result
description: The validation results contained in a validation report.

name: shapes graph well-formed
description: If true then the validation engine was certain that the shapes graph has passed all SHACL syntax requirements during the validation process.

name: detail
description: Links a result with other results that provide more details, for example to describe violations against nested shapes.

name: focus node
description: The focus node that was validated when the result was produced.

name: result message
description: Human-readable messages explaining the cause of the result.

name: result path
description: The path of a validation result, based on the path of the validated property shape.

name: result severity
description: The severity of the result, e.g. warning.

name: source constraint
description: The constraint that was validated when the result was produced.

name: source shape
description: The shape that is was validated when the result was produced.

name: source constraint component
description: The constraint component that is the source of the result.

name: value
description: An RDF node that has caused the result.

name: shapes graph
description: Shapes graphs that should be used when validating this data graph.

name: entailment
description: An entailment regime that indicates what kind of inferencing is required by a shapes graph.

name: path
description: Specifies the property path of a property shape.

name: inverse path
description: The (single) value of this property represents an inverse path (object to subject).

name: alternative path
description: The (single) value of this property must be a list of path elements, representing the elements of alternative paths.

name: zero or more path
description: The (single) value of this property represents a path that is matched zero or more times.

name: one or more path
description: The (single) value of this property represents a path that is matched one or more times.

name: zero or one path
description: The (single) value of this property represents a path that is matched zero or one times.

name: parameter
description: The parameters of a function or constraint component.

name: label template
description: Outlines how human-readable labels of instances of the associated Parameterizable shall be produced. The values can contain {?paramName} as placeholders for the actual values of the given parameter.

name: optional
description: Indicates whether a parameter is optional.

name: validator
description: The validator(s) used to evaluate constraints of either node or property shapes.

name: shape validator
description: The validator(s) used to evaluate a constraint in the context of a node shape.

name: property validator
description: The validator(s) used to evaluate a constraint in the context of a property shape.

name: and
description: RDF list of shapes to validate the value nodes against.

name: class
description: The type that all value nodes must have.

name: node kind
description: Specifies the node kind (e.g. IRI or literal) each value node.

name: closed
description: If set to true then the shape is closed.

name: datatype
description: Specifies an RDF datatype that all value nodes must have.

name: ignored properties
description: An optional RDF list of properties that are also permitted in addition to those explicitly enumerated via sh:property/sh:path.

name: max count
description: Specifies the maximum number of values in the set of value nodes.

name: disjoint
description: Specifies a property where the set of values must be disjoint with the value nodes.

name: equals
description: Specifies a property that must have the same values as the value nodes.

name: has value
description: Specifies a value that must be among the value nodes.

name: in
description: Specifies a list of allowed values so that each value node must be among the members of the given list.

name: language in
description: Specifies a list of language tags that all value nodes must have.

name: less than
description: Specifies a property that must have smaller values than the value nodes.

name: less than or equals
description: Specifies a property that must have smaller or equal values than the value nodes.

name: max exclusive
description: Specifies the maximum exclusive value of each value node.

name: max inclusive
description: Specifies the maximum inclusive value of each value node.

name: max length
description: Specifies the maximum string length of each value node.

name: min count
description: Specifies the minimum number of values in the set of value nodes.

name: min exclusive
description: Specifies the minimum exclusive value of each value node.

name: min inclusive
description: Specifies the minimum inclusive value of each value node.

name: min length
description: Specifies the minimum string length of each value node.

name: node
description: Specifies the node shape that all value nodes must conform to.

name: not
description: Specifies a shape that the value nodes must not conform to.

name: or
description: Specifies a list of shapes so that the value nodes must conform to at least one of the shapes.

name: pattern
description: Specifies a regular expression pattern that the string representations of the value nodes must match.

name: flags
description: An optional flag to be used with regular expression pattern matching.

name: property
description: Links a shape to its property shapes.

name: qualified max count
description: The maximum number of value nodes that can conform to the shape.

name: qualified value shape
description: The shape that a specified number of values must conform to.

name: qualified value shapes disjoint
description: Can be used to mark the qualified value shape to be disjoint with its sibling shapes.

name: qualified min count
description: The minimum number of value nodes that must conform to the shape.

name: unique languages
description: Specifies whether all node values must have a unique (or no) language tag.

name: exactly one
description: Specifies a list of shapes so that the value nodes must conform to exactly one of the shapes.

name: ask
description: The SPARQL ASK query to execute.

name: construct
description: The SPARQL CONSTRUCT query to execute.

name: select
description: The SPARQL SELECT query to execute.

name: update
description: The SPARQL UPDATE to execute.

name: prefixes
description: The prefixes that shall be applied before parsing the associated SPARQL query.

name: constraint (in SPARQL)
description: Links a shape with SPARQL constraints.

name: default value
description: A default value for a property, for example for user interface tools to pre-populate input fields.

name: description
description: Human-readable descriptions for the property in the context of the surrounding shape.

name: group
description: Can be used to link to a property group to indicate that a property shape belongs to a group of related property shapes.

name: name
description: Human-readable labels for the property in the context of the surrounding shape.

name: order
description: Specifies the relative order of this compared to its siblings. For example use 0 for the first, 1 for the second.

name: target
description: Links a shape to a target specified by an extension language, for example instances of sh:SPARQLTarget.

name: return type
description: The expected type of values returned by the associated function.

name: result annotation
description: Links a SPARQL validator with zero or more sh:ResultAnnotation instances, defining how to derive additional result properties based on the variables of the SELECT query.

name: annotation property
description: The annotation property that shall be set.

name: annotation value
description: The (default) values of the annotation property.

name: annotation variable name
description: The name of the SPARQL variable from the SELECT clause that shall be used for the values.

name: filter shape
description: The shape that all input nodes of the expression need to conform to.

name: nodes
description: The node expression producing the input nodes of a filter shape expression.

name: intersection
description: A list of node expressions that shall be intersected.

name: union
description: A list of node expressions that shall be used together.

name: expression
description: The node expression that must return true for the value nodes.

name: rule
description: The rules linked to a shape.

name: condition
description: The shapes that the focus nodes need to conform to before a rule is executed on them.

name: subject
description: An expression producing the resources that shall be inferred as subjects.

name: predicate
description: An expression producing the properties that shall be inferred as predicates.

name: object
description: An expression producing the nodes that shall be inferred as objects.

name: JavaScript constraint
description: Constraints expressed in JavaScript.

name: JavaScript function name
description: The name of the JavaScript function to execute.

name: JavaScript library
description: Declares which JavaScript libraries are needed to execute this.

name: JavaScript library URL
description: Declares the URLs of a JavaScript library. This should be the absolute URL of a JavaScript file. Implementations may redirect those to local files.

name: And constraint component
description: A constraint component that can be used to test whether a value node conforms to all members of a provided list of shapes.

name: Class constraint component
description: A constraint component that can be used to verify that each value node is an instance of a given type.

name: Closed constraint component
description: A constraint component that can be used to indicate that focus nodes must only have values for those properties that have been explicitly enumerated via sh:property/sh:path.

name: Datatype constraint component
description: A constraint component that can be used to restrict the datatype of all value nodes.

name: Disjoint constraint component
description: A constraint component that can be used to verify that the set of value nodes is disjoint with the the set of nodes that have the focus node as subject and the value of a given property as predicate.

name: Equals constraint component
description: A constraint component that can be used to verify that the set of value nodes is equal to the set of nodes that have the focus node as subject and the value of a given property as predicate.

name: Has-value constraint component
description: A constraint component that can be used to verify that one of the value nodes is a given RDF node.

name: In constraint component
description: A constraint component that can be used to exclusively enumerate the permitted value nodes.

name: Language-in constraint component
description: A constraint component that can be used to enumerate language tags that all value nodes must have.

name: Less-than constraint component
description: A constraint component that can be used to verify that each value node is smaller than all the nodes that have the focus node as subject and the value of a given property as predicate.

name: less-than-or-equals constraint component
description: A constraint component that can be used to verify that every value node is smaller than all the nodes that have the focus node as subject and the value of a given property as predicate.

name: Max-count constraint component
description: A constraint component that can be used to restrict the maximum number of value nodes.

name: Max-exclusive constraint component
description: A constraint component that can be used to restrict the range of value nodes with a maximum exclusive value.

name: Max-inclusive constraint component
description: A constraint component that can be used to restrict the range of value nodes with a maximum inclusive value.

name: Max-length constraint component
description: A constraint component that can be used to restrict the maximum string length of value nodes.

name: Min-count constraint component
description: A constraint component that can be used to restrict the minimum number of value nodes.

name: Min-exclusive constraint component
description: A constraint component that can be used to restrict the range of value nodes with a minimum exclusive value.

name: Min-inclusive constraint component
description: A constraint component that can be used to restrict the range of value nodes with a minimum inclusive value.

name: Min-length constraint component
description: A constraint component that can be used to restrict the minimum string length of value nodes.

name: Node constraint component
description: A constraint component that can be used to verify that all value nodes conform to the given node shape.

name: Node-kind constraint component
description: A constraint component that can be used to restrict the RDF node kind of each value node.

name: Not constraint component
description: A constraint component that can be used to verify that value nodes do not conform to a given shape.

name: Or constraint component
description: A constraint component that can be used to restrict the value nodes so that they conform to at least one out of several provided shapes.

name: Pattern constraint component
description: A constraint component that can be used to verify that every value node matches a given regular expression.

name: Property constraint component
description: A constraint component that can be used to verify that all value nodes conform to the given property shape.

name: Qualified-max-count constraint component
description: A constraint component that can be used to verify that a specified maximum number of value nodes conforms to a given shape.

name: Qualified-min-count constraint component
description: A constraint component that can be used to verify that a specified minimum number of value nodes conforms to a given shape.

name: Unique-languages constraint component
description: A constraint component that can be used to specify that no pair of value nodes may use the same language tag.

name: Exactly one constraint component
description: A constraint component that can be used to restrict the value nodes so that they conform to exactly one out of several provided shapes.

name: SPARQL constraint component
description: A constraint component that can be used to define constraints based on SPARQL queries.

name: Expression constraint component
description: A constraint component that can be used to verify that a given node expression produces true for all value nodes.

name: JavaScript constraint component
description: A constraint component with the parameter sh:js linking to a sh:JSConstraint containing a sh:script.

name: Blank node
description: The node kind of all blank nodes.

name: Blank node or IRI
description: The node kind of all blank nodes or IRIs.

name: Blank node or literal
description: The node kind of all blank nodes or literals.

name: IRI
description: The node kind of all IRIs.

name: IRI or literal
description: The node kind of all IRIs or literals.

name: Literal
description: The node kind of all literals.

name: Blank node
description: The node kind of all blank nodes.

name: Blank node or IRI
description: The node kind of all blank nodes or IRIs.

name: Blank node or literal
description: The node kind of all blank nodes or literals.

name: IRI
description: The node kind of all IRIs.

name: IRI or literal
description: The node kind of all IRIs or literals.

name: Literal
description: The node kind of all literals.

name: Info
description: The severity for an informational validation result.

name: Violation
description: The severity for a violation validation result.

name: Warning
description: The severity for a warning validation result.

name: this
description: A node expression that represents the current focus node.
